 how companies can cope with real trade-offs, innovating around them or even thriving within them. Suggesting that the shared-value mindset may actually get in the way of progress, bestselling author Sarah Kaplan shows in The 360° Corporation how trade-offs, rather than being confusing or problematic, can actually be the source of organizational resilience and transformation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCorporationsxSocial aspects. 0aIndustrial management. 0aSocial responsibility of business. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Management.2bisacsh  aCorporate social responsibility.  ainnovation.  ashared value.  astakeholders.  atrade-offs.  atransformation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2020 Englishz978311070479208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2020z9783110704624oZDB-23-DBV08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503610439423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503610439.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070479-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DBVb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020